e. However, using the test class as a config might not be idiomatic, despite existing patterns. There's also concern about native image reflection metadata — if the metadata for the test class isn't present, it could lead to failures of the native image runtime during tests. And if the harness lacks an agent, reachability metadata becomes a concern.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing service registry issues**\\n\\nI need to consider if Class.newInstance is being called at serviceRegistry.getService(...), especially if the service is already cached. Creating a new registry per config seems okay. But there’s a potential issue: registry.getService might not lazily instantiate a service without \\\"StandardServiceInitiators\\\" included, even though ReactiveServiceRegistryBuilder does include them. It's important to clarify that tests are not run. Should I mention metadata, though? The developer advised against compiling or running tests myself, which I didn't do. So, I need to finalize this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Added a dedicated test for the active dynamic-access class:\n\n- `tests/src/org.hibernate.reactive/hibernate-reactive-core/2.0.7.Final/src/test/java/org_hibernate_reactive/hibernate_reactive_core/SqlClientPoolConfigurationInitiatorTest.java`\n\nThe test configures `Settings.SQL_CLIENT_POOL_CONFIG` with a public custom `SqlClientPoolConfiguration` implementation via the normal `ReactiveServiceRegistryBuilder` API, then requests the `SqlClientPoolConfiguration` service. This should exercise:\n\n- `org.hibernate.reactive.pool.impl.SqlClientPoolConfigurationInitiator.initiateService`\n- the remaining uncovered `Class#newInstance()` call site on line 39\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e9bf31f8b1ea3f7016a15eb0c8d24819080f2f32921d80436\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 25326, "output": 61